    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail, peel your <strong>parsnip[s]</strong> into quarters lengthways, then into batons</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice half your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>into discs and peel, then chop your <strong>red</strong> <strong>onion[s] </strong>in half, then cut <strong>half</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-beef-and-mango-chutney-pie-with-mustard-seed-veg/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped vegetables</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 20-25 min or until golden and tender</p><p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>carrot</strong></p><p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>remaining onion</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-beef-and-mango-chutney-pie-with-mustard-seed-veg/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>diced carrot </strong>to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-beef-and-mango-chutney-pie-with-mustard-seed-veg/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and carrot is starting to soften, turn the heat up to high, then add your<strong> mince</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Once browned, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>mango chutney </strong>and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1-2 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-beef-and-mango-chutney-pie-with-mustard-seed-veg/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)<strong> </strong>and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and reduce the heat to medium-high, then cook for 3-4 min further or until the sauce has thickened</p><p>Once thickened, season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and transfer to an <strong>oven-proof</strong> <strong>dish</strong> (cooking for 2 or more? Use individual dishes for fancy presentation!) \u2013 this is your<strong> pie mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-beef-and-mango-chutney-pie-with-mustard-seed-veg/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface generously with <strong>flour</strong>,<strong> </strong>unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong>, roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a<strong> rolling pin </strong>and cut to the size of your pie dish[es], then lay it over the dish[es], trim off any excess (use for fancy pie decorations!) and press the edges with a fork to seal the pastry to the dish[es]</p><p>Brush with a little <strong>water</strong>, add a few <strong>black mustard seeds</strong> to the top (you'll use the rest later!), then put in the oven for 15-20 min or until puffed up, golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>mince & mango chutney pie</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-beef-and-mango-chutney-pie-with-mustard-seed-veg/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After the initial 20-25 min, remove the tray[s] with the chopped vegetables from the oven, add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and the <strong>remaining black mustard seeds</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 5 min \u2013 this is your <strong>mustard seed veg</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-beef-and-mango-chutney-pie-with-mustard-seed-veg/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> spiced</strong> <strong>mince & mango chutney pie</strong> with the <strong>mustard seed veg</strong> topped with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped coriander </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
